<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,711,909]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
<keyLead pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
1. Body with dark reddish-brown or reddish-brown colouration (
<figureCitation box="[932,1039,711,736]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[160,227,1366,1389]" captionTargetBox="[162,1148,150,1331]" captionTargetId="figure-77@4.[162,1154,142,1335]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi, 1974. (a,b) Holotype male in dorsal and lateral views, respectively; (c) labels; (d,e) male habitus in dorsal and lateral views, respectively; (f) female habitus in dorsal view. (a,b) pictures out of scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758317/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figures 1</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[1055,1071,711,736]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[160,225,1740,1763]" captionTargetBox="[178,1132,148,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-3@6.[166,1149,142,1708]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov. (a,b) Habitus of holotype male in dorsal and lateral views, respectively; (c) habitus of female paratype in dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758321" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758321/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">3</figureCitation>
). Frons rugopunctate in female (
<figureCitation box="[486,589,746,771]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="14.[160,225,1441,1464]" captionTargetBox="[168,1146,144,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-42@14.[166,1149,142,1410]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 11. Detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs of females in dorsal view: (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi;(b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedi sp.nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Arrow indicates punctate frons in (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758341/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(a,b)). Juxtasutural interstriae with large and dense punctures scattered from anterior to posterior elytral area (
<figureCitation box="[874,983,780,805]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[160,225,1189,1212]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,146,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-100@15.[166,1149,142,1157]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. Females of Gibboryctes species with detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs in lateral view and left elytra in dorsal view, respectively. (a,b) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (c,d) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (e,f) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov. Jsi, juxtasutural interstria. Arrow indicates coalescent punctures in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758343/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 12</figureCitation>
(b,f))................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,711,909]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
<keyLead pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
- Body with black colour (
<figureCitation box="[517,633,815,840]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[160,225,1050,1073]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,191,1006]" captionTargetId="figure-170@5.[162,1154,142,1018]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov. (a, b) Habitus of paratype female in dorsal and lateral views, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758319" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758319/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 2a</figureCitation>
). Frons punctate in female (
<figureCitation box="[994,1109,815,840]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="14.[160,225,1441,1464]" captionTargetBox="[168,1146,144,1407]" captionTargetId="figure-42@14.[166,1149,142,1410]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figure 11. Detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs of females in dorsal view: (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi;(b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedi sp.nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Arrow indicates punctate frons in (b)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758341" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758341/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(b)). Juxtasutural interstriae with large punctures scarce and confined to anterior elytral area (
<figureCitation box="[271,379,884,909]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[160,225,1189,1212]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,146,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-100@15.[166,1149,142,1157]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. Females of Gibboryctes species with detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs in lateral view and left elytra in dorsal view, respectively. (a,b) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (c,d) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (e,f) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov. Jsi, juxtasutural interstria. Arrow indicates coalescent punctures in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758343/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 12</figureCitation>
(d)). Male unknown.. 
<taxonomicName authority="Duarte and Grossi" authorityName="Duarte and Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[621,1061,884,909]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ebeninus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[621,852,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Gibboryctes ebeninus</emphasis>
Duarte and Grossi
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1069,1156,884,909]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,938,1136]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
<keyLead pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
2. Labrum subtrapezoidal, with broadly rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[841,940,938,963]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="9.[160,225,1090,1113]" captionTargetBox="[166,1145,146,1050]" captionTargetId="figure-188@9.[166,1149,142,1058]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 6. Labrum in dorsal view. (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758331/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(c)). Galea broadly rounded at apex (
<figureCitation box="[413,507,972,997]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1161,1184]" captionTargetBox="[167,1127,143,1126]" captionTargetId="figure-61@11.[166,1149,142,1129]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Right maxilla in ventral view. (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Red arrows indicating triangular galea in (a), elongate maxillary palpomere II in (b), lobed inner margin of galea and stipe with triangular lobe in (c), pointed and triangular teeth on galea in (d), scythe-shape d teeth and rounded inner margin of galea in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758335/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(c)). Punctures on the anterior pronotal corners predominantly coalescent (
<figureCitation box="[419,524,1007,1032]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[160,225,1189,1212]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,146,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-100@15.[166,1149,142,1157]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. Females of Gibboryctes species with detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs in lateral view and left elytra in dorsal view, respectively. (a,b) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (c,d) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (e,f) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov. Jsi, juxtasutural interstria. Arrow indicates coalescent punctures in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758343/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 12</figureCitation>
(e))......... 
<taxonomicName authority="Duarte and Grossi" authorityName="Duarte and Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[625,1061,1007,1032]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Gibboyctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="endroedii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[625,852,1007,1032]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Gibboyctes endroedii</emphasis>
Duarte and Grossi
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1069,1156,1007,1032]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,1156,938,1136]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
<keyLead pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
- Labrum subtriangular (
<figureCitation box="[470,565,1042,1067]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="9.[160,225,1090,1113]" captionTargetBox="[166,1145,146,1050]" captionTargetId="figure-188@9.[166,1149,142,1058]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 6. Labrum in dorsal view. (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758331/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 6</figureCitation>
(a)). Galea triangular (
<figureCitation box="[813,908,1042,1067]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="11.[160,225,1161,1184]" captionTargetBox="[167,1127,143,1126]" captionTargetId="figure-61@11.[166,1149,142,1129]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figure 8. Right maxilla in ventral view. (a) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (b) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (c) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov.; (d) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell; (e) Tetragus waldenfelsi (Endrödi). Red arrows indicating triangular galea in (a), elongate maxillary palpomere II in (b), lobed inner margin of galea and stipe with triangular lobe in (c), pointed and triangular teeth on galea in (d), scythe-shape d teeth and rounded inner margin of galea in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758335/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 8</figureCitation>
(a)). Punctures on the pronotal corners predominantly contiguous (
<figureCitation box="[716,816,1076,1101]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[160,225,1189,1212]" captionTargetBox="[167,1149,146,1154]" captionTargetId="figure-100@15.[166,1149,142,1157]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. Females of Gibboryctes species with detail of head, pronotum and prothoracic legs in lateral view and left elytra in dorsal view, respectively. (a,b) Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi; (c,d) Gibboryctes ebeninus sp. nov.; (e,f) Gibboryctes endroedii sp. nov. Jsi, juxtasutural interstria. Arrow indicates coalescent punctures in (e)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758343/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 12</figureCitation>
(a))...................................................... ............................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Endrodi" authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1974" box="[837,1155,1111,1136]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="szelenyii">
<emphasis box="[837,1060,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Gibboryctes szelenyii</emphasis>
Endrödi
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
