<subSubSection lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="215" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[160,678,1212,1239]" box="[160,678,1212,1239]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
<heading bold="true" box="[160,678,1212,1239]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,678,1212,1239]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
Notes on natural history of 
<taxonomicName box="[526,678,1212,1239]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[526,678,1212,1239]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Gibboryctes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[159,1156,1266,1707]" lastBlockId="25.[159,1156,142,237]" lastPageId="25" lastPageNumber="215" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">
Specimes of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1974" box="[298,511,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="szelenyii">
<emphasis box="[298,511,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Gibboryctes szelenyii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi, 2022" authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[567,693,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Gibboyctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="endroedii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[567,693,1266,1291]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">G. endroedii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[700,784,1266,1291]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
were collected inside of epigeous termite nests (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1882" box="[309,415,1300,1325]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Blattodea</taxonomicName>
:Isoptera: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[519,638,1300,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Termitidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Blattodea" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Termitidae</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1974" box="[651,862,1300,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="szelenyii">
<emphasis box="[651,862,1300,1325]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Gibboryctes szelenyii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found to be associated with many termite species (see remarks under 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1974" box="[664,777,1335,1360]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="szelenyii">
<emphasis box="[664,777,1335,1360]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">G. szelenyii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Termites were not collected from the nests where specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[490,615,1370,1395]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Gibboyctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="endroedii">
<emphasis box="[490,615,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">G. endroedii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were found. The localities of nests are marked by shrub vegetation and rocky outcrops characteristic of open areas of savannah and rupestrian grasslands (
<figureCitation box="[287,391,1439,1464]" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1389,1412]" captionTargetBox="[168,1146,235,1354]" captionTargetId="figure-89@18.[166,1149,142,1357]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 15. (a) Rupestrian grassland; (b) rock outcrops." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758349" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758349/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 15</figureCitation>
(a,b)). Adults, pupae and larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Endrodi" authorityYear="1974" box="[765,879,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="szelenyii">
<emphasis box="[765,879,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">G. szelenyii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi, 2022" authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[937,1063,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Gibboyctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="endroedii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[937,1063,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">G. endroedii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1070,1156,1439,1464]" pageId="24" pageNumber="214" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
were found occupying the central portion of nests (
<figureCitation box="[709,810,1474,1499]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1035,1058]" captionTargetBox="[166,1148,142,1003]" captionTargetId="figure-194@19.[166,1149,142,1003]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 16. (a) Adult of Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi at central portion of termite nest (arrow); (b) detail of the adult in situ (arrow); (c) pupal chamber with its structures in the shape of pellets (arrow); (d) recently emerged adult." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758351/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 16</figureCitation>
(a–d)). When handled, the larvae emitted a stridulation sound produced by friction among the mandibles and maxillae. Furthermore, the larvae were observed building rigid galleries structured with faeces and saliva.The pupal chamber is also quite rigid,perhaps to avoid termite attacks (
<figureCitation box="[974,1073,1578,1603]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="19.[160,225,1035,1058]" captionTargetBox="[166,1148,142,1003]" captionTargetId="figure-194@19.[166,1149,142,1003]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 16. (a) Adult of Gibboryctes szelenyii Endrödi at central portion of termite nest (arrow); (b) detail of the adult in situ (arrow); (c) pupal chamber with its structures in the shape of pellets (arrow); (d) recently emerged adult." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758351" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758351/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="214">Figure 16</figureCitation>
(c)).The larval excrement, when dried, acquires a peculiar aspect similar to ‘pellets’, flattened and subrectangular, with almost straight corners (90-degree angles),and which can be considered a diagnostic character for generic identification. This discovery represents the first record of an Oryctini associated with a termite nest. Regarding 
<taxonomicName authority="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi, 2022" authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" box="[730,855,142,167]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="215" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ebeninus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[730,855,142,167]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="215">G. ebeninus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[866,955,142,167]" pageId="25" pageNumber="215" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, only adults were collected, in an area under a 
<taxonomicName box="[481,592,177,202]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Eucalyptus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[481,592,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="215">Eucalyptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
crop where a 
<collectingRegion box="[753,893,177,202]" country="United States of America" name="Pennsylvania" pageId="25" pageNumber="215">Pennsylvania</collectingRegion>
light trap was installed, which perhaps attracted the specimens.
</paragraph>
